    <string name="help_text"><![CDATA[
        <p>
          miNWos displays the networks and cellular state of your device.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the top is the <span style="background:#F6E6FF">phone state</span> which contains data
          about your cellular network and is global and singular. Below it is a list of all the
          networks currently available to your device, which may include Wi-Fi, cellular data and
          others.
        </p>
        <p>
          <font face="monospace">NOT_METERED</font> and
          <font face="monospace">TEMPORARILY_NOT_METERED</font> are flags that indicate the
          network\'s current capabilities. For more information, see
          <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/net/NetworkCapabilities">
            <font face="monospace">NetworkCapabilities</font> in the Android documentation</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The default (active) network is always at the top and
          <span style="background:#FFFFD0">highlighted yellow</span>. On some devices, only the
          default network can be displayed.
        </p>
        <p>
          The list is updated automatically when available networks change. Press the &#128260;
          button to trigger a manual update.
        </p>
        <p>
          Use <i>Toggle notification</i> to show or hide a persistent notification that displays
          information about the default (active) network even when the app is not in the foreground.
        </p>
    ]]></string>
